    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Every byte needs 2 characters to be encoded into hex format. If you specify an odd number of hex characters, that means that somewhere half a byte is missing. Old versions of Geth probably didn't enforce this and padded the blob with a zero at the beginning.\r\n\r\nWhilst there are some cases when more flexibility *can* be correct (e.g. if the byte blob has `0000` as the first 4 bits), generally it's more common that someone copy-pastes a hex string and accidentally doesn't select all of it. By enforcing proper lengths we can ensure that accidental copy-paste errors don't slip by unnoticed.",
